Great 👍 now let’s clearly understand Path Variable in Spring MVC (very important 🔥)

🔷 🔥 What is Path Variable?

👉 Data passed inside URL path, not after ?

http://localhost:8080/book/101

👉 Here:

101 = path variable
🔷 🔥 How to Use in Spring

👉 Use @PathVariable

✅ Example (Your Book App - Delete)
@GetMapping("/delete/{id}")
public String deleteBook(@PathVariable int id) {

    service.deleteBook(id);

    return "redirect:/books";
}
🔥 URL Call
/delete/5

👉 Spring does:

id = 5
🔷 🔥 Example (Edit)
@GetMapping("/edit/{id}")
public String editBook(@PathVariable int id, Model model) {

    Book book = service.getBookById(id);

    model.addAttribute("book", book);

    return "books";
}
🔷 🔥 HTML Link
<a th:href="@{'/edit/' + ${b.id}}">Edit</a>
<a th:href="@{'/delete/' + ${b.id}}">Delete</a>
What is this?
